Spilo/Patroni PostgreSQL Replication Configuration:
https://github.com/zalando/spilo/blob/master/ENVIRONMENT.rst - Spilo environment variables including PGUSER_STANDBY
https://github.com/zalando/postgres-operator/issues/1220 - Common replication user configuration issues
https://github.com/zalando/spilo/blob/master/postgres-appliance/scripts/configure_spilo.py - Shows pg_hba.conf template for standby user
https://github.com/patroni/patroni/issues/2315 - Patroni dynamically manages pg_hba.conf, don't edit manually
https://www.dbi-services.com/blog/troubleshooting-patroni-cluster-pg_hba-configuration-not-applied/ - Patroni configuration precedence
https://patroni.readthedocs.io/en/latest/patroni_configuration.html - Official Patroni configuration documentation

CRITICAL INSIGHTS:
- Spilo uses PGUSER_STANDBY='standby' and PGPASSWORD_STANDBY='standby' by default
- Patroni dynamically generates pg_hba.conf - NEVER edit manually
- Use postgresql.pg_hba section in patroni.yml to configure replication access
- Patroni configuration precedence: Defaults → YAML → Environment Variables

