etcd Troubleshooting and Management:
https://etcd.io/docs/v3.5/op-guide/recovery/ - etcd disaster recovery
https://etcd.io/docs/v3.5/dev-guide/api_reference_v3/ - etcd v3 API reference
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/administer-cluster/configure-upgrade-etcd/ - Kubernetes etcd administration

CRITICAL TROUBLESHOOTING INSIGHTS:
- kubectl commands hanging for specific namespaces usually indicate operator/webhook issues
- Use kubectl -v=8 to debug API server communication and identify where requests hang
- Patroni "waiting for leader to bootstrap" with "Lock owner: None" = DCS connectivity/state issues
- Clear stale etcd cluster state with v3 API deleterange when reinitializing Patroni clusters
- StatefulSets create pods sequentially - first pod must be ready before next pod starts


